o_projectreactor_tools.blockhound, outside the library. Also, I think I should keep the java.security.manager property in the JVM Test as it could simplify security management for Java 21, but there might be some issues with the security manager after the test runs.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Addressing constructor ambiguity**\\n\\nI'm thinking that maybe Java's compile process is complaining about the reference to `super(null, null...)` being ambiguous. The constructor signature is all method references, and using null seems fine, but I wonder if I need an import. After some consideration, I realize I probably don't need one. I’m also considering if I could define `private abstract static class ExposedDirect extends Dispatcher.Direct` without a constructor, but it's likely that would lead to a compile error.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Clarifying file inspection**\\n\\nI'm considering whether to inspect the untracked file with read access. My instinct says no, especially since I might want to include tests that haven't been run due to specific instructions. I think it’s important to finalize this process to ensure everything is in order. Balancing these aspects is tricky, but clarity about what to include or skip is key in deciding how to proceed effectively.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "Implemented focused coverage for the active dynamic-access class.\n\nChanges:\n- Added dedicated test file:\n  - `tests/src/io.projectreactor.tools/blockhound/1.0.8.RELEASE/src/test/java/io_projectreactor_tools/blockhound/ClassInjectorInnerUsingReflectionInnerDispatcherInnerDirectTest.java`\n- The test exercises `ClassInjector$UsingReflection$Dispatcher$Direct` paths for:\n  - `initialize`\n  - `findClass`\n  - `defineClass`\n  - `getDefinedPackage`\n  - `getPackage`\n  - `definePackage`\n- Updated JVM test configuration to allow SecurityManager installation so the `initialize()` permission-check path can be reached:\n  - `tests/src/io.projectreactor.tools/blockhound/1.0.8.RELEASE/build.gradle`\n\nNotes:\n- I did not run tests, per instruction.\n- There was an existing modified file in the worktree that I did not touch:\n  - `NexusAccessorInnerDispatcherInnerCreationActionTest.java`", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_02310933e049a01b0169fab0043fd881a3bb9011cf86843fe3\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 379, "output": 986, "cacheRead": 28672, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 30037, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1778036725174, "responseId": "resp_02310933e049a01b0169faaff5b1d081a3a70e8928d84930c8"}, "toolResults": []}
