t that runs under JDK 21. I need to ensure that class files compile correctly for both Java 25 and the native image.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering test toolchain setup**\\n\\nI'm thinking that I might set the `Test` javaLauncher to a specific path for the Java toolchain, pointing to `/usr/lib/jvm/java-21-openjdk-amd64`, but not for the native image. I’m also pondering how this will affect compiling class files to the right version. I need to ensure everything is compatible, but it's a bit tricky figuring out the best configuration. I wonder if this approach will help avoid potential issues down the line.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Configuring Java settings**\\n\\nI need to remove the Java block and add configurations for JavaCompile and Test tasks with the proper launcher. I don't think I need to worry about imports. I'm checking if `javaToolchains` should exist in the build; it should be fine since the Java plugin from TCK is likely there. I’m wondering if I should use `options.release = 21` or `options.release.set(21)` in Groovy Gradle — both might work anyway. Let's confirm the existing setup.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_CfBJStsAufsLWCdLWdXP77ft|fc_02310933e049a01b0169fab0ea80c081a3ab9305ed4836a850", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "rg -n \"options\\.release|javaLauncher = javaToolchains\" tests/src -g build.gradle | head -50", "timeout": 10}, "partialJson": "{\"command\":\"rg -n \\\"options\\\\.release|javaLauncher = javaToolchains\\\" tests/src -g build.gradle | head -50\",\"timeout\":10}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 732, "output": 1437, "cacheRead": 59392, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 61561, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778036949574, "responseId": "resp_02310933e049a01b0169fab0d6173481a39da88b231f47eaf2"}}
